bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I am an experienced caregiver with 12 years of dedicated service in childcare. I am CPR certified, ensuring that your children are in safe hands at all times. I also assist with homework and assignments, making your evenings a little less hectic. In addition, I can help with light housework, so you can come home to a clean and organized space. Whether it's picking up the kids from school, guiding them through their studies, or helping around the house, I am here to support your family's needs.

description.originalText: Angel has been an absolute lifesaver for our family. She's not only incredibly reliable but also fantastic with our kids. They love spending time with her, and we feel so secure knowing they're in such capable hands. Highly recommend!

bio.experienceSummary: I love to read, cook, and have fun with the little ones! I've always been around children, and always had a heart for the youth, for they are the next generation! Every child deserves to be loved and treated as such! I can travel just about anywhere so distance isn't really an issue! I also help with pets, walking, feeding, playing! I do my best to accommodate to the parents request! I look forward to meeting you!

description.originalText: He is a great caregiver. He is patient and very trustworthy. My son loves him and does so well compared to previous babysitters that I have worked with in the past.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello, I m a charismatic, loving, and responsible care giver. Full time loving sitter for your family. 4+ years experience under my belt, along with CCI certifications, valid child abuse clearances, along with clean background and driving records. I enjoy working with children, it is so very rewarding. I have experience with newborns, toddlers, grade school and preteen children. I believe all children, despite age, need love, attention and structure, someone who will set rules and boundaries, but will also be a fun time and let them enjoy themselves! I also am EXTREMELY experienced in elder/hospice/companion care too! I work for JFCS and have had numerous cases. Ranging from elders who needed help with errands and companion care all the way up to those seeking more help with showering, toilwting, dressing, etc. I have a million sources and come highly recommended!

As a dedicated childcare provider with over a decade of experience, my passion for nurturing young minds and supporting families drives my every action. My journey into childcare began with fulfilling babysitting roles, where I discovered the profound impact I could have on children's lives. Since then, I've dedicated myself to providing reliable, high-quality childcare that allows parents peace of mind.

My patient, calm, and creative nature allows me to connect effortlessly with children of all ages. I believe in fostering a nurturing environment where children feel safe to explore, learn, and grow. Open communication is essential to me, so parents can expect regular updates about their child's day and any matters that arise.

I'm comfortable caring for up to three children simultaneously and have experience with a wide range of age groups. From infants to preteens, I tailor my approach to meet each child's individual needs and developmental stage.

description.originalText: From the moment Shelice started working with my family, we knew we had found the right person. She is incredibly patient, kind, and compassionate, always going above and beyond to ensure mychild is comfortable and happy. Shelice’s ability to anticipate my son and I needs and provide timely assistance is truly remarkable.  She is also a great communicator, keeping us informed and involved in the care plan.  We are so grateful for her dedication and care."

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello My name is Kyra and I am a student at Emory University who currently works at the Clifton school! I'm passionate about nurturing children's growth and making a positive impact on their lives. With five years of experience caring for children, I'm skilled in creating a safe and nurturing environment where they can thrive. I communicate openly with parents to ensure their needs are met and I'm very comfortable enforcing household rules.

My creative and imaginative personality shines through my interactions with children. We enjoy playing educational games that promote learning, technology-based games and apps, and games that foster creativity. I believe learning should be fun and engaging, and I strive to make every moment a teachable one.

I'm comfortable caring for up to four children, ranging from infants to preteens. I also have a car and am comfortable with pets. If you're seeking a reliable, experienced, and passionate childcare provider, I'm here to help your family thrive

I'd describe my personality as kind, caring, and fun! 

I like working with kids because every day is different and there's nothing more rewarding than helping kids. 

I started working with kids when I was about 18 years old. I've been a single night babysitter, a full-time nanny, and everything in between.

In my spare time, I like to hang out with friends, spend time with family, and travel!

With over 20 years of dedicated experience as a Baby Nurse, I am passionate about providing exceptional care and support to families during the crucial first months after birth. I specialize in training babies to sleep through the night, ensuring that both baby and family enjoy restful nights and peaceful days.

description.displayText: Meschelle came in with a wealth of experience and helped us, being new parents, to navigate the do's and don't of taking care of an infant. We appreciated how detail oriented she was which helped sleep train our first child.
description.originalText: Meschelle came in with a wealth of experience and helped us, being new parents, to navigate the do's and don't of taking care of an infant. We appreciated how detail oriented she was which helped sleep train our first child.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi my name is Jadah. I recently graduated from The George Washington University. I'm available for child care, home sitting and pet sitting. 

I've always loved kids because their creativity is so refreshing and I believe they can teach me as much as I can teach them. I've had experience ranging from new borns all the way up to school age children. 

My responsibilities have included school pick up, homework help, snacks, crafts, and dinner/ bedtime if needed. 

I'm open to light house cleaning and errand running. All pets welcome.

description.originalText: Jadah has cared for our baby twice a week from ages 4 months-6 months. She is always on time and is a great communicator. She is very engaging with our baby, and our daughter lights up whenever she walks in the door. Jadah will be a fantastic asset to any family!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I hold a master's degree in IO Psychology and five years of experience in ABA. I'd love to connect and explore how we can work together to support your loved one!

description.displayText: I am cautious when it comes to caring for my youngest child.  She is very caring and my youngest child does not like a lot of people but Kyra is not like a lot of people. She's caring and gives attention to all three of my children.
description.originalText: I am cautious when it comes to caring for my youngest child.  She is very caring and my youngest child does not like a lot of people but Kyra is not like a lot of people. She's caring and gives attention to all three of my children.

bio.experienceSummary:
Being around children it's truly a joy for me. As a mother of a 6yr and as an experienced nanny, I've been able to connect with many wonderful families. Learning about child development and the science behind child behavior has been a fascinating journey for me. My Bachelors degree in Behavioral Science from Mercy College and my experience as a mother have truly expanded my understanding of child psychology. 

As your nanny, my mission is to keep your children safe, happy and stimulated by providing a nurturing environment and facilitating activities to foster their creative nature, individual interest and personality. Whether it's pretend play, singing, dancing, crafts, sports, nature exploration or science experiment. Also, as a native Spanish speaker and experienced Spanish tutor, I'll be thrilled to incorporate Spanish if you desire.

description.displayText: Our little ones got to enjoy Sheila for 5 months (10 hours a day!) and we are all going to miss her now that she's moving so far :( she was great with stimulating their minds and bodies, always keeping them active and happy!
